<TEXT>
   George A. Strichman 72, former Chairman of Colt
Industries Inc., died Monday of cancer.
   Before joining Colt in 1963, he was president of ITT Kellogg.
   Strichman led a reorganization of Colt through acquisition and
divestiture, dropping some of its firearms manufacturing and adding
aerospace equipment.
   He was also chairman of overseers of the Jewish Theological
Seminary of America and a member of its board of directors.
Strichman was also chairman of the Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute.
