<FIRST>r a PM-PA-Super7-JackpotList     04-26 0203</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-PA-Super 7-Jackpot List,0215</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-Lottery Fever, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Pennsylvania's North American record lottery jackpot of at least
$100 million dwarfs the previous top 10.
   Spain's El Gordo, or ``the fat one,'' boasts the world's richest
lottery jackpot. A $159 million first prize last December was split
by hundreds of people.
   A $100 million Pennsylvania Super 7 jackpot, if won by one
person tonight, would mean almost $3.85 million a year for 26 years
for the winner.
   Marc Narducci, editor of Lottery Player's Magazine, Moorestown,
N.J., compiled a list of the top 10 previous jackpots in North
America. These are the U.S. state lottery jackpots, followed by the
jackpot figure, the date, and the number of winning tickets:
   1. Illinois, $69,948,000, April 15, 1989, four
   2. California, $61.98 million, Oct. 29, 1988, three
   3. Florida, $55.1 million, Sept. 3, 1988, one
   4. California, $51.4 million, June 4, 1988, two
   5. Pennsylvania, $46 million, Oct. 14, 1987, one
   6. New York, $45 million, Dec. 3, 1988, 12
   7. California, $44.88 million, March 3, 1989, four
   8. California, $41.58 million, Jan. 21, 1989, seven
   9. Florida, $41.42 million, April 22, 1989, two
   10. New York, $41 million, Aug. 21, 1985, three
</TEXT>
