<FIRST>r i PM-Colombia-Crash     04-26 0160</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Colombia-Crash,0165</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cargo Plane Crashes Into Slum; Seven Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A cargo jet plunged into a slum area
near the coastal city of Barranquilla today, killing all five
people on board and two on the ground, the Civil Aeronautics
Administration said.
   Eleven people on the ground were injured, and five houses were
destroyed, the government agency reported.
   The plane, a twin-engine Caravelle of the Colombian airline
Aerosucre, took off from the Barranquilla airport at 2:42 a.m.,
according to the release.
   One of the engines failed two minutes after takeoff, and as the
plane tried to make it back to the airport the other engine failed,
a spokesman with the control tower in Barranquilla said in a
broadcast interview with the Bogota radio station RCN.
   A man and a child were killed on the ground, the agency said. It
said all those killed on the plane were crew members.
   Barranquilla is about 400 miles north of Bogota.
</TEXT>
