<FILEID>AP-NR-04-26-89 1213EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>u a PM-HighwayKillings     04-26 0242</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Highway Killings,0250</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ninth Victim of Serial Killer Believed Found</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MARION, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Investigators today said they believe a
young woman found dead along Interstate 195 is the ninth victim of
a New Bedford-area serial killer.
   Bristol County District Attorney Ronald A. Pina ``would be very
surprised if this were not a victim'' of the killer who left the
bodies of eight women along southeastern Massachusetts highways,
said Jim Martin, a spokesman for Pina.
   The woman was under 30 and had been dead 10 to 12 months, he
said. The body, found Monday, will be checked against dental
records of three missing women to identify the victim, Martin said.
   Investigators linked the body to the other killings because of
where it was found, the position of the body, certain evidence
found at the scene and information gleaned from the autopsy
Tuesday, the spokesman said.
   He would not be more specific about the findings.
   The autopsy, which was to continue today, did not immediately
determine the cause of death, he said. Bristol County investigators
have declined to say how seven of the eight other victims died.
They have said one was strangled.
   The eight victims so far identified all had links to New
Bedford's Weld Square area, a district known for drugs and
prostitution. The first of the bodies was found in July.
   The body of the apparent ninth victim was found in Plymouth
County, about six miles from New Bedford.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
