<FIRST>r i AM-Venezuela-Colombia     04-26 0139</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Venezuela-Colombia,0146</SECOND>
<HEAD>Band of Colombians Attack Venezuelan Military Post</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 20 armed Colombians infiltrated
Venezuelan territory and attacked a military patrol Wednesday,
killing one national guardsman and wounding three, military
spokesmen said.
   Gen. Fernando Ochoa, national guard commander in Maracaibo, said
the attack occurred outside a national guard post at Mata de Coco,
about 400 miles west of the capital city of Caracas, at 7 a.m.
   He said authorities were not certain if the men were bandits or
guerrillas.
   ``Whoever they were, they stole five automatic FAL rifles,''
Ochoa said.
   The Belgian-made rifles are used by the Venezuelan military.
   Ochoa said military patrols were combing the area looking for
the assailants.
   Mata de Coco is on the Colombian-Venezuelan border. Venezuelan
forces accuse the Colombian gunmen of kidnapping local cattle
ranchers and sabotaging oil installations.
