   Mid-April car and light truck sales by the eight
major U.S. automakers rose 5.4 percent over last year in an
apparent indication that incentives are working, the companies said.
   The companies reported Tuesday that they sold an average of
41,380 vehicles a day during the April 11-20 period this year,
compared with an average 39,257 during the same time last year.
   Car sales were up 3.7 percent while truck sales rose 8.6 percent.
