   Tuesday's announcement was the latest indication that the
aerospace giant is continuing on a roll of large aircraft orders.
   It came just one day after Boeing's annual shareholders meeting,
at which the plane manufacturer announced increased dividends and a
stock split, and predicted record-breaking sales this year.
</TEXT>
