<TEXT>
   Speculators surveyed by one of the country's
largest brokerage firms say they have not changed the way they do
business despite the government's investigation of activities at
the Chicago Board of Trade and the Chicago Mercantile Exchange.
   Eighty percent of more than 1,100 private speculators who
responded to the Lind-Waldock &amp; Co. survey said disclosure of the
FBI probe on Jan. 23 had not affected their trading methods, the
brokerage firm reported Tuesday.
   Sixty-three percent said they thought the futures exchanges
could do a better job of policing themselves.
</TEXT>
