<FIRST>r f BC-UPIBroadcasting     04-26 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-UPI Broadcasting,0193</SECOND>
<HEAD>UPI Launches New Broadcasting Subsidiary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   United Press International says it has formed
a wholly owned subsidiary, UPI Broadcasting Inc., to operate its
English and Spanish-language broadcast services.
   UPI President Paul Steinle said Tuesday the new organization
``will allow our broadcast operations to run as a
bottom-line-oriented business, managed by someone responsible not
only for quality but also for its business success.''
   A search was under way for a president to head the subsidiary,
UPI said.
   UPI Broadcasting will develop and expand the UPI Radio Network
and UPI Radio Noticias, as well as develop other potential
broadcast enterprises.
   ``This new organizational arrangement, which reaffirms our
commitment to the broadcasting industry, gives our radio operation
the prominence it deserves _ both in terms of long-term strategy
and of daily operational needs,'' Steinle said.
   Earlier this year UPI implemented a new sales strategy for
radio, with special UPI component news products being offered to
broadcasters.
   As part of the establishment of UPI Broadcasting, UPI also is
launching a syndicated Spanish-language radio service effective
June 1 to replace its barter Spanish-language network.
</TEXT>
