<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Chemicals     04-26 0165</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Chemicals,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>DuPont First-quarter Profits Up 25 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   DuPont Co. said Wednesday its
first-quarter earnings rose 25 percent over last year with strong
performances in the company's petroleum and industrial products
subsidiaries.
   DuPont reported net income of $736 million, or $3.08 a share,
compared with $590 million, or $2.45 a share, in the same 1988
period.
   Sales increased 10 percent to $8.7 billion from $7.9 billion in
last year's first quarter.
   ``The results reflect very good performance across most of the
company's businesses, with a particularly large gain in the
petroleum segment,'' outgoing company chairman Richard E. Heckert
said at the company's annual meeting.
   Edgar S. Willard took over today as chairman and chief executive
officer of the chemical giant.
   Earnings in DuPont's petroleum subsidiary nearly doubled to $217
million from $112 million a year ago. The company's industrial
products division reported a 51.5 percent earnings gain, to $147
million from $97 million. Fibers, polymers and coal also showed
increases.
</TEXT>
