   It was the lowest rate since two-year notes averaged 9.08
percent on Jan. 25. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of
9\ percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,983.90.
   A total of $9.26 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$22.9 billion.
