<HEAD>Interior To Lease Acreage In Six Southern States</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Bureau of Land Management will lease
about 325,000 acres in 600 parcels for oil and gas exploration in
six southern states at a sale Thursday.
   According to BLM spokesman Charles Most, the states and total
acreage are Alabama, 180,000 acres; Arkansas, 32,000 acres;
Florida, 54,816 acres; Louisiana, 899 acres; Mississippi, 40,467
acres; and Virginia, 13,402 acres.
   Interior Secretary Manuel Lujan is expected at the sale along
with Sen. J. Bennett Johnston (D-La.), chairman of the Energy and
Natural Resources Committee.
   All the acreage is within national forests, except 3,691 acres
on an Army Corps of Engineers water reservoir project in Virginia,
Most said.
   He said the leases are for five years.
