<SECOND>AM-Earns-Computers,0170</SECOND>
<HEAD>Compaq First-Quarter Earnings Up 78 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Compaq Computer Corp., citing strong sales
overseas, on Wednesday reported first-quarter profits of $83
million, up 78 percent from the $47 million in the same period a
year ago.
   The earnings, which amounted to $1.95 per share, up from $1.21
per share last year, were based on sales of $683 million, up 55
percent from $439 million in the three-month period ending March
31, 1988.
   In spite of the big gain, Compaq's stock fell because of
statements by the company to analysts that forecasts of $8 a share
in 1989 earnings were aggressive though achievable.
   The stock fell $1.50 a share to $77.75 in consolidated New York
Stock Exchange trading.
   ``Compaq sales outside North America were particularly strong,
accounting for 46 percent of first-quarter revenue,'' Rod Canion,
president and chief executive officer, said in a written statement.
   Sales of some products were limited by lack of supply, Canion
said.
