<SECOND>BC-Petroleum Review,0484</SECOND>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Total crude runs to stills averaged 13,002,000
barrels daily during the week ended Friday, April 21, the American
Petroleum Institute reported Wednesday. This compared with
13,025,000 barrels daily in the previous week and 13,186,000
barrels daily a year ago.
   Crude runs east of California averaged 10,320,000 barrels daily
compared with 10,468,000 the previous week and 10,532,000 a year
ago.
   Motor gasoline production for the latest week amounted to
6,820,000 barrels a day, compared with 6,704,000 barrels a day in
the previous week and 6,919,000 a day a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline production was 5,586,000 a day
compared with 5,584,000 a day last week and 5,705,000 a day a year
ago.
   Motor gasoline stocks at the end of the latest week were
222,990,000 barrels, versus 225,426,000 a week earlier and
225,610,000 a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline stocks totaled 196,280,000
barrels compared with 199,226,000 in the previous week and
196,594,000 barrels last year.
   Daily average gross crude oil and lease condensate production
for the week ended Friday was 7,848,000 barrels compared with
8,236,000 last year.
   Crude oil stocks totaled 329,677,000 barrels at the close of
last week, against 320,557,000 a week previous and 356,958,000 a
year ago.
   East of California crude stocks amounted to 251,873,000 barrels,
compared with 259,766,000 a week earlier.
   Daily imports east of California for the week ended Friday were
crude oil, 5,360,000 barrels, residual fuel oil, 520,000,
distillate fuel oil, 351,000, and others 993,000, a total of
7,224,000 barrels.
   California imports were: crude oil 375,000 barrels, and products
77,000, a total of 452,000 barrels, for a grand total of 7,676,000.
   For the four weeks, daily imports east of California were crude
oil 5,087,000 barrels, residual fuel oil 283,000, distillate fuel
oil 205,000, and others 591,000, for a total of 5,088,000 barrels.
   For the four weeks, California daily imports averaged for crude
oil 237,000 barrels, products 69,000, a total of 306,000 barrels,
for a grand total of 5,394,000.
